<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 12:53:46 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人更有可能说特朗普不太信教或根本不信教</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/16/americans-have-become-more-likely-to-say-trump-is-not-too-or-not-at-all-religious/</link><description>在特朗普最坚定的支持者中，相对较少的人表示他们认为他非常虔诚。只有 8% 的共和党人和 5% 的白人福音派人士认为情况确实如此。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 01:22:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/16/americans-have-become-more-likely-to-say-trump-is-not-too-or-not-at-all-religious/</guid></item><item><title>美国人因对国家政治制度的悲观态度而在国际上脱颖而出</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/americans-stand-out-internationally-for-their-pessimism-about-the-nations-political-system/</link><description>高收入国家的人们通常不太可能说他们国家的政治制度需要重大改变或彻底改革。美国人是个例外。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 01:25:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/americans-stand-out-internationally-for-their-pessimism-about-the-nations-political-system/</guid></item><item><title>青少年使用 TikTok、Instagram 和 Snapchat 的体验</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/04/15/teens-experiences-on-tiktok-instagram-and-snapchat/</link><description>青少年大多转向 TikTok、Instagram 和 Snapchat 寻找乐趣和联系。但关于消息传递、屏幕时间和网络欺凌的体验各不相同。以及青少年如何评价这些网站如何影响他们的心理健康。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 01:10:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/04/15/teens-experiences-on-tiktok-instagram-and-snapchat/</guid></item><item><title>多项指标显示2025年美国民主健康状况下降</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/multiple-indicators-show-a-decline-in-the-health-of-americas-democracy-in-2025/</link><description>大多数美国人表示，美国的民主曾经是其他国家效仿的好榜样，但近年来却并非如此。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:55:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/multiple-indicators-show-a-decline-in-the-health-of-americas-democracy-in-2025/</guid></item><item><title>近年来，美国人对中国的看法变得更加积极</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</link><description>大多数美国人仍然对中国持负面看法，但最近的一项调查显示，对中国的好感度有所上升，尤其是在民主党人和年轻人中。现在称中国为敌人的人越来越少了。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</guid></item><item><title>当地新闻情况说明书</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/fact-sheet/local-news-fact-sheet/</link><description>自 2016 年以来，美国人对当地新闻的关注度有所下降。探索当今人们如何获取当地新闻，从电视和印刷媒体转向数字来源。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:04:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/fact-sheet/local-news-fact-sheet/</guid></item><item><title>美国大多数新数据中心都将落户农村地区</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/13/most-new-data-centers-in-the-us-are-coming-to-rural-areas/</link><description>全国正在建设超过 1,500 个新数据中心。大多数将建在农村地区，特别是南部和中西部，标志着从城市地点的转变。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2026 01:22:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/13/most-new-data-centers-in-the-us-are-coming-to-rural-areas/</guid></item><item><title>美国人仍然选择纸质书籍而不是数字或音频版本；很少有人参加读书俱乐部</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/09/americans-still-opt-for-print-books-over-digital-or-audio-versions-few-are-in-book-clubs/</link><description>大多数美国成年人都读书，尽管电子书和有声读物的使用有所增长，但纸质书仍然比数字格式更受青睐。习惯因人群而异，很少有人参加读书俱乐部。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 01:18:35 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/09/americans-still-opt-for-print-books-over-digital-or-audio-versions-few-are-in-book-clubs/</guid></item><item><title>最高法院多久推翻自己的判决？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/08/how-often-does-the-supreme-court-overturn-its-own-decisions/</link><description>只有不到 1% 的最高法院案件推翻了旧的判决。其中一半以上案件涉及经济活动或刑事诉讼。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 01:07:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/08/how-often-does-the-supreme-court-overturn-its-own-decisions/</guid></item><item><title>视频：民意调查能告诉我们谁会在选举日获胜吗？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/04/08/video-can-polls-tell-us-who-will-win-on-election-day/</link><description>我们经常听到候选人领先、落后，或者比赛打平。这是基于“赛马”民意调查，该民意调查根据人们如何回答选举前的调查来估计候选人的支持率。但由于某些原因，准确测量赛马情况非常困难。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 00:52:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/methods/2026/04/08/video-can-polls-tell-us-who-will-win-on-election-day/</guid></item></channel></rss>